Compiles cleanly. Here's the fix.

## The bug

In the tmux TUI's Enter/spawn handler (`src/cli/tmux_cli.rs`), when you spawned a new session on a spawnable agent, the project was resolved from the **TUI process's current working directory**:

```rust
let project = crate::project::resolve(
    &std::env::current_dir().unwrap_or_default(),
);
```

So no matter which project tab you had selected, the spawn always went into whatever directory you launched the TUI from. The daemon's `spawn_agent` → `project_abs_path` → `get_project_path(project)` then correctly maps the project name to its dir — but it was being handed the *wrong* project name to begin with.

## The fix

Use the selected project tab (`pf`, the active tab's project filter) as the project, only falling back to cwd-resolution on the "all projects" tab where there's no filter:

```rust
let project = pf.map(str::to_string).unwrap_or_else(|| {
    crate::project::resolve(&std::env::current_dir().unwrap_or_default())
});
```

Now spawning from a project tab creates the session in that project's directory.

One note: on the "all projects" tab (no tab filter), there's no selected project, so it still falls back to cwd. If you want spawning from that view to be disallowed or to prompt for a project instead, let me know — but the per-tab case (your reported scenario) is now correct.

